  "description": "Swedish merchant and Vice Consul. Born in Visby on June 6, 1884, the son of Vice Consul CJ B. Björkander and Henrietta Wallér. Married Märta BoHn in 1910 and they had two children, Maj and Ivar. He completed a vocational course at Gothenburg's School of Business in 1903-04 and worked in Bremen in 1904-05. He joined his father's company in Visby in 1905, became a partner in 1909, and restructured it into AB CJ Björkander & Son. From 1912 onwards, he was the managing director of the firm. Björkander served as the Russian Consul General from 1908 and then as the Russian Vice Consul from 1912 to 1916. He was appointed as the British Vice Consul in 1922. Björkander was an active member of the Visby community and served as a member of City Council, Vice-chairman of the Harbour Board, and a County council member for the conservative party. Björkander passed away on September 19, 1958." 
